Folded optics is the term that refers to a new technology in digital cameras that uses a prism to allow for high optical zoom in a small camera body design. The first (and so far) only camera to take advantage of folded optics is the Panasonic Lumix DMC-TZ1. The camera is similar in side to standard 3x and 4x optical zoom cameras, but can zoom up to 10x thanks to folded optics.